description:
&lt;p&gt;Join our friendly and dynamic team delivering Sleep services and Respiratory Services to our patients in Hywel Dda University Health Board, based at Prince Philip Hospital, Llanelli.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a committed and motivated respiratory physiologist and this is an ideal vacancy for someone who is newly qualified, or expecting to qualify this year.&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidate will be encouraged and supported to manage their own caseload providing:&lt;br /&gt;• Sleep diagnostics, APAP/CPAP therapy and ongoing diagnostic, maintenance and support to the patient&lt;br /&gt;• Respiratory diagnostics using the latest equipment.&lt;br /&gt;Newly qualified physiologists will be supported by a friendly team, strong leadership and opportunity to gain experience and develop skills both within The Sleep Unit and the Cardio-Respiratory Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a candidate who shares our values and commitment to ensuring the quality of our services. We encourage open engagement in service design and delivery, and seek an individual eager to share knowledge and ideas in an open and friendly forum.&lt;br /&gt;Hywel Dda is situated in a beautiful part of West Wales with areas of outstanding natural beauty with award winning beaches and National Parks, ideal for all outdoor activity especially surfing and walking. The area is rich in heritage and history, consequently attracting thousands of tourists each year. There are vibrant social communities that can help you find a better work life balance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on 16th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
